article.headline: N.J. Tech 67, South Dakota St. 62
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Clayton Barker scored 19 of his game-high 27 points in the second half as N.J. Tech held on for a 67-62 win over South Dakota State on Thursday night. Kraig Peters added 11 points for the Highlanders (4-18), who snapped a five game losing streak with the win. Matt Caldwell scored 22 points for the Jackrabbits (5-18), who trailed most of the game and were down by as much as 13 points in the second half before rallying in the closing minutes. Caldwell hit his fifth 3-pointer to cut the lead to 64-62 with 23 seconds left to play. The Jackrabbits, though, couldn't get another score and Andrew Engel then made three free throws -- the final two with five seconds left -- to seal the win. Michael Loney added 11 points and Kai Williams finished with 10 points and a game-high nine rebounds for South Dakota State, which lost its third straight game.
